  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Rehabilitate 300 Cacao Farms in Southern Belize</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project&apos;s aim is to rehabilitate 400+ acres of active cacao farms using integrated agro-forestry systems; to educate farmers in management techniques that will reduce the incidence of Monilia disease, which is devastating to cacao trees; and finally to improve cacao yields through such techniques of regular pruning. A total of 300 farmers in 25 mayan communities will benefit directly from the implementation of the project.</narrative>
  </description>
